        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model form acceptance criteria — physics representativeness",
        "description": "Model must capture geometric nonlinearity (large-deformation kinematics), nonlinear material response (bilinear isotropic hardening for Ti-6Al-4V), and frictional contact at screw-rod and rod-UHMWPE interfaces. Sensitivity of QoIs to contact friction coefficient (μ = 0.1–0.4) must be documented. Achieved: all three physics are included; friction sensitivity documented in the sensitivity analysis report."
      },
      "rationale": "The FEA model incorporates large-deformation kinematics (NLGEOM ON), a bilinear isotropic hardening material model for Ti-6Al-4V ELI (E = 114 GPa, σ_y = 880 MPa, E_t = 2.3 GPa) calibrated to tensile coupon data, and augmented Lagrange frictional contact (μ = 0.2) at all metallic interfaces and a frictionless contact at the rod-UHMWPE block interface consistent with lubricated test conditions. A sensitivity study varying μ from 0.1 to 0.4 showed < 3% variation in stiffness and < 5% variation in yield force, confirming that the nominal μ = 0.2 choice does not dominate QoI uncertainty. Model form is judged representative of the dominant physics. Gradation 3 achieved and required."
