        "name": "Test conditions acceptance criteria — multiple loading conditions",
        "description": "Validation testing should cover at least two distinct ASTM F1717 loading conditions (e.g., compression-bending and torsion, or two compression-bending span lengths) to demonstrate model generalizability across the operating envelope. Achieved Gradation 2: only a single compression-bending condition (50 mm UHMWPE block spacing) was tested; torsion and alternative span lengths were not included in this COU."
      },
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted under a single ASTM F1717 static compression-bending configuration with 50 mm UHMWPE block spacing, which is the standard regulatory submission condition. Torsional loading and alternative block spacings (e.g., 30 mm, 70 mm) were not included in this validation activity due to resource constraints and because the regulatory submission requires only the standard configuration. This limits the generalizability assessment to a single loading mode, resulting in Gradation 2 rather than the required Gradation 3. An offset rationale is documented in the decision record, noting that the single-condition validation is consistent with FDA guidance for 510(k) submissions for this device class and that the model's physical fidelity (Gradation 3 model form) provides confidence in extrapolation."
