        "description": "The validation metric E/u_val must be < 1.96 (95% confidence threshold) for all three QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement), AND the mean absolute percentage difference must be < 10% for each QoI. Both criteria must be satisfied simultaneously. Achieved: E/u_val = 0.84, 1.21, 1.53; mean differences = 2.1%, 4.8%, 8.4% respectively — all within bounds."
      },
      "rationale": "Quantitative output comparison was performed using the ASME V&V 40 validation metric E/u_val for all three QoIs. Results: stiffness E/u_val = 0.84 (mean diff = 2.1%), yield force E/u_val = 1.21 (mean diff = 4.8%), force-at-40mm E/u_val = 1.53 (mean diff = 8.4%). All three QoIs satisfy both the E/u_val < 1.96 and < 10% mean difference acceptance criteria. The force-at-40mm QoI shows the largest discrepancy, attributed to post-yield geometric nonlinearity sensitivity, but remains within acceptance bounds. Gradation 3 achieved and required."
