        "description": "Each QoI must be directly traceable to a clinical failure mode or regulatory requirement. Stiffness maps to construct rigidity affecting fusion outcome; yield force maps to onset of permanent deformation (implant failure); force at 40 mm maps to catastrophic failure threshold per ASTM F1717. All three QoIs must appear in the 510(k) submission performance testing section. Achieved: all three QoIs are included in the DePuy Synthes 510(k) submission and traceable to clinical risk analysis failure modes."
      },
      "rationale": "The three QoIs (construct stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are the primary performance endpoints specified in ASTM F1717 and directly referenced in the FDA 510(k) submission for this device. Construct stiffness is clinically relevant to spinal fusion success; yield force identifies onset of permanent implant deformation; force at 40 mm represents a catastrophic failure surrogate. All three QoIs are traceable to failure modes in the device risk analysis (ISO 14971 FMEA, risk item IDs R-007, R-012, R-019). Gradation 3 achieved and required."
