      },
      "rationale": "The validation activity is a direct implementation of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending using production-representative non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs — the same device, loading mode, test standard, and boundary conditions as the COU. The FEA model was developed specifically to represent the ASTM F1717 test configuration, not a surrogate geometry. No substantive deviations from COU conditions were identified. The two-laboratory design strengthens the relevance assessment by demonstrating reproducibility of both experimental and simulation results across independent facilities. Gradation 3 achieved and required."
